survey.comments: the required column accepts a javascript expression that evaluates to true or false. A blank cell defaults to false. If true, the form cannot be submitted unless it is answered and the user cannot progress to the next question

survey.comments: constraint is used to make sure legal values are entered. In this case, the answer to age cannot be negative. If it is, when the user tries to move on the constraint message will be displayed
survey.name: age

survey.comments: When using required with prompts nested in if statements, instead of simply writing true, copy the condition for the if statement
survey.name: marital_status

display.hint: 0 if never away, or less than two weeks.
